<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Somalia on New Year's Eve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, January 1 (Xinhua) -- At least two people were
killed and two more wounded during an attack by gunmen in
Hawlwadag district in South Mogadishu, Somali on New Year's eve.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, the deceased included a man and his
son, while his wife was seriously wounded.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen attacked the household using hand grenades and
rocket propelled grenades, the eyewitnesses said, adding that a
donkey used for transporting water for the family was also killed.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the attack is not known officially. However, a
relative of the attacked family said the gunmen were annoyed by
the fact that the owner of the house was among a group of elders
called for testifying in a dispute over a piece of land in the
vicinity.
</P>
<P>
The owner of the house has testified against the claim of the
gunmen over the ownership of the land, the relative said.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of astonished people gathered around the destroyed
family Saturday, helping them with the little they could afford.
</P>
<P>
The land ownership disputes in Mogadishu have claimed many
lives these days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
