<DOCNO> XIE20000101.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Bourses Operate on New Year's Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's two bourses
functioned on Saturday, the first day of the new year, the new
century and the new millennium, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The Dhaka Stock Exchange (DSE) and the Chittagong Stock
Exchange were possibly the only stock exchanges in the world that
opened on Saturday, the New Year's day.
</P>
<P>
No Y2K problem was reported from the two bourses.
</P>
<P>
In Bangladesh, the stock exchanges operate on Saturdays, the
second day of the country's two-day weekly holiday.
</P>
<P>
The DSE All Share Price Index ended up 1.39 points, or 0.28
percent, at 489.16 on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 137 issues were traded in the DSE, with 88 advancing
in value, 36 posting losses and 13 others changing hands at
previous prices.
</P>
<P>
But the volume fell by 24.5 percent to 1.563 million securities
from the previous day's 2.072 shares, and the turnover in value
fell by 40.4 percent to 80 million taka (1.57 million U.S. dollars)
from 134.2 million taka (2.63 million dollars) the previous day.
</P>
</TEXT>
