<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1400 GMT, January 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI -- Sixteen people died on New Year's Eve in a road
accident in Bungoma District in western Kenya when a lorry they
were traveling in rolled several times, local media reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that twelve passengers died on the spot Friday
while three others died at hospital. 15 people were admitted to
the hospital in critical condition.  (Kenya-Lorry Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan and India Saturday exchanged lists of
their respective nuclear installations and facilities through
diplomatic channels, a press release by the Foreign Office here
said.
</P>
<P>
The lists are exchanged on the first working day of every year
under an agreement signed by Pakistan and India in 1988 on
prohibition of attacks against each other's nuclear installations
and facilities.  (Pakistan-India-Nuke)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran announced Saturday that it did not face any
problem caused by the millennium bug (Y2K) as it entered the new
millennium.
</P>
<P>
The Millennium Information Dissemination Committee (MIDC) at
the Interior Ministry said that the condition at all parts and
organizations of the country were reported normal.  (Iran-Y2K)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- There were 795 cases of firecracker-related injuries
and 47 cases of stray bullets in millennium celebrations in the
Philippines by Saturday morning, said an official.
</P>
<P>
Health Secretary Alberto Romualdez told reporters here Saturday
that the surveillance period started 10 days ago and will end on
January 4, and 68 hospitals are involved in this surveillance
activity.  (Philippines-Injuries)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Four Lebanese soldiers were killed and two others
missing in a military clash with an Islamist militant group
Saturday night in the country's second largest city of Tripoli.
</P>
<P>
An army statement issued Monday morning said militants from the
radical Takfir and Hijrah group ambushed an army patrol near
Ghassoun town on the outskirts of the country's northern-most city
of Tripoli.  (Lebanon-Clash-Militants)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM -- Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa has called
for harder work and more self-reliant in an effort to alleviate
poverty in the new year.
</P>
<P>
In his New Year message delivered to the nation at the new year
eve, Mkapa stressed that the debt relief and economic recovery
programs would not rid the country of all its problems.  (
Tanzania-Message)
</P>
