<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- A passenger ship unable to
navigate through heavy fog crashed into a freighter Friday evening
on the Yangtze River, killing one person and leaving another two
missing.
</P>
<P>
By 3:15 a.m.today, more than 600 passengers on board had been
rescued, according to reports from rescue teams at the scene.
</P>
<P>
The Jianghan No. 21 passenger ship rammed into a trial
container ship at about 6:30 p.m. yesterday while enroute to Luhe
County of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Forty of the passengers on board were children, according to
the reports.
</P>
<P>
