province and Nanjing, the provincial capital, sent rescue teams to
the spot. Huang Zhengdong, minister of Communications, rushed to
the rescue headquarters to oversee the recovery operations.
</P>
<P>
At 7:30 p.m., a team of officials from the provincial
communications department, marine supervision bureau and police
arrived on the scene.
</P>
<P>
Three towing ships and a rescue ship which can accommodate 1,
700 people were able to anchor alongside the passenger ship. The
last batch of people from the Jianghan No. 21 were rescued and
returned to the Nanjing Port early this morning. 
