<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Millennium Bug Attacks Uganda Banks: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Commercial banks and credit
institutions operating in Uganda have found no millennium bug
attacking their computer systems, a report said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report of the computer status, based on post-millennium
rollover tests conducted between 00:30 and 12:00 hours on the
first day of the new century, proves that all the computer systems
have been working normally.
</P>
<P>
"As of 13:00 on January 1, 2000, returns had been received from
20 of the 21 supervised financial institutions. The returns
indicate that none of these institutions have experienced a
problem with any of their mission-critical systems after the date
changed," the two-page report said.
</P>
<P>
However, further comprehensive tests shall be conducted and are
scheduled to complete on January 3 to ensure that there will be
nothing wrong with critical systems.
</P>
<P>
Uganda set up its national Y2K task force early last year to
ensure the computers operating in the key sectors of the country
are not vulnerable to attacks from the millennium bug and its
related viruses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
