<TEXT>

<P>
Beijing, January 1, 2000 (Xinhua) -- The following is the
photo list on January 1, 2000 released by Xinhua:

1. Soldiers salute the Chinese National flag as the first sunlight
of the new millennium lights China's outpost in Fuyuan county,
northeast Heilongjiang province, at 7:04 am January 1, 2000.

2. More than 10,000 people watch the first flag raising ceremony
in the new millennium at the Tiananmen Square in Beijing at 7:36
am, January 1, 2000. The flag used in the ceremony had been
carried into the space by China's first experimental spacecraft
Shenzhou.

3. Zhang Yiming, a baby boy, is brought up by an unidentified
nurse just after his birth at 0:03:30 January 1, 2000 at the
Beijing Gynaecology and Obstetrics Hospital in Beijing. The lucky
boy, with the weight of 3900g and length of 53mm, was recognized
as the " Millenim Baby" just after the birth.

4. Zhang Yiming has the first photo taken with his father Zhang
Wei and mother Shi Jialin at the Beijing Gynaecology and
Obstetrics Hospital. Zhang Yiming was born at 0:03:30 January 1,
2000 at the hospital in Beijing. The lucky boy, with the weight of
3900g and length of 53mm, was recognized as the "Baby of Thousands
Year" just after the birth.

5. Sailors wave to the first light of the new millenimu on the
battleship "Huai Yang" Saturday January 1, 2000 at a Navy base in
Shanghai.

6. Two new-couples try to hang red flowers on the branches of a
snowy tree to wish a happy life Saturday January 1, 2000 in
Changchun, capital of north China's Jilin province. 21 new-couples
celebrate their wedding day at the first day of the new thousand
years.

7. Pigeons fly over the sky of Shitang, which is lighted by the
first sunlight on China's mainland, at 6:46 January 1, 2000.
Shitang township of east China's Zhejiang province is the spot
geographically qualified to greet the first sunlight in China.
More than 300,000 people viewed the exciting sun-rising.

8. Liu Xiaoman, local peasant of Hainan province, transplant the
rice seedling with her mother and sister at the Tengqiao township,
Sanya city of south China's Hainan province Saturday January 1,
2000.

9. Thousands of lamps light the night of construction site of the
Three Gorges Water Conservancy of Yangtze River on the new year
eve. The people on the site welcome the new thousand year with
their unique way.

10. Chinese President Jiang Zemin, also General Secretary of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, visits the
nation's newest and biggest set of bells, The Harmony Bells, at
the Working People's Palace Saturday January 1, 2000 in Beijing.
</P>
