<HEADLINE> India's Exports Up 30.72 percent in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- India's exports went up by 30.
72 percent to 3.34 billion U.S. dollars in November, the Ministry
of Commerce said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Cumulative exports in the first eight months (April-November)
of the current fiscal year grew by 12.71 percent to 24.19 billion
dollars while imports during the period grew by 7.15 percent at 30.
24 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The country's exports, which began the financial year with a
measly 2.09 percent growth in April, gaining momentum in August
and have maintained double-digit growth since then.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the trade deficit narrowed slightly to 6.04 billion
dollars in the first eight months of the current fiscal year
despite a surging oil import bill. 
