<DOCNO> XIE20000101.0033 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Y2K Hitch Reported In India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- India has rolled over to the
new millennium without any major Y2K hitch reported as the key
sectors like power, banking, railways and aviation switched over
to the new year shortly after midnight.
</P>
<P>
The first successful test relieved the fears of many in the
country over the so-called "millennium bug" and India's
preparedness for the rollover.
</P>
<P>
The Reserve Bank of India (RBI), the central bank of the
country, said in a statement Friday night that its computer
systems had rolled over to the year 2000 without any disruption.
</P>
<P>
RBI announced on Saturday that all banking operations would be
conducted normally next Tuesday, in view of the continuation of
its function systems which had not seen any hitch after the
switchover to the new year.
</P>
<P>
The State Bank of India (SBI), accounting for one-fourth of the
country's banking industry, also reported very smooth transition
of its computer systems.
</P>
<P>
SBI official said that all of its 1,934 computerized branches
at 342 centers completed the close of the day procedures Friday
night and the start of the day procedures Saturday free from any
bug.
</P>
<P>
Airport officials also reported the smooth rollover Saturday as
special cells set up by the government-run Indian Airlines and Air
India, and the Airport Authority of India to monitor the rollover
have certified that the "systems are fine."
</P>
<P>
Even as eight international airlines canceled their flights
during Friday night, 14 Indian flights were in the air, of which
six flights crossed the midnight barrier at local time, a
spokesman for Air India said.
</P>
<P>
Indian power authorities said in a press release that the power
sector entered the new year without any Y2K problem.
</P>
<P>
First reports from Indian railways and the defense sector
indicated that all departments concerned rolled over "smoothly and
successfully" to the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Oil and Natural Gas Cooperation reported that its Y2K
compliance program had succeeded in plugging the Y2K bug and
ensured the uninterrupted flow of oil and gas from the wells in
the western offshore.
</P>
<P>
Major stock exchanges, which remained closed Saturday, are
scheduled to conduct mock trading on Sunday before they start
their first trading sessions next Monday.
</P>
<P>
The National Information Center, which monitored 11 critical
sectors, had received reports that computer systems throughout the
country are functioning without any glitches. 
</P>
