<HEADLINE> CPPCC Throws Tea Party to Greet New Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today reiterated that the "one China" principle is the foundation
of peaceful reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark at a New Year's tea party hosted by the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) in Beijing this morning.
</P>
<P>
"China will not sit idle and tolerate any act calculated to
split China, pursue the so-called 'independence of Taiwan,' or
harm the fundamental interests of the Chinese people on both sides
of the Taiwan Straits," said Jiang, who is also general secretary
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
chairman of the Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
While extending New Year's greetings on behalf of the Chinese
central government to people from all walks of life, compatriots
in Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan, as well as foreign friends, Jiang
reviewed major achievements China made in 1999 and said the year
2000 was the last year of the Ninth Five-Year Plan.
</P>
<P>
He urged all people of the country, under the leadership of the
CPC, to correctly understand the situation, recognize the tasks
ahead, seize the opportunities, and be progressive, determined and
united in the country's socialist construction cause.
</P>
<P>
In the wake of the return of Hong Kong and Macao to China,
solving the Taiwan issue and the final reunification of the
Chinese sovereign territory have become more and more prominent in
the eyes of all Chinese, Jiang continued.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that the China adheres to the principles of peaceful
reunification and "one country, two systems," and the eight-point
proposals he put forward five years ago regarding expanding
relations across the Taiwan Straits and promoting the process of a
peaceful reunification remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
"We will take into consideration the different characteristics
of Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, and Taiwan will be given plenty of
flexibility to realize peaceful reunification of China under the '
one country' premise," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The tea party was presided over by CPPCC National Committee
Chairman Li Ruihuan. Jiang Zhenghua, chairman of the Central
Committee of Chinese Peasants and Workers Democratic Party (CPWDP),
also delivered a speech at the gathering, which was attended by
other high-ranking Chinese officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
