<HEADLINE> 4 Lebanese Soldiers Killed in Clash with Militants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Four Lebanese soldiers were killed
and two others missing in a military clash with an Islamist
militant group Saturday night in the country's second largest city
of Tripoli.
</P>
<P>
An army statement issued Monday morning said militants from the
radical Takfir and Hijrah group ambushed an army patrol near
Ghassoun town on the outskirts of the country's northern-most city
of Tripoli.
</P>
<P>
Four soldiers were killed in the exchange of fire, an officer
and a soldier were still missing, the statement added.
</P>
<P>
It said the army patrol came to the site after getting
information that some members of the Takfir and Hijrah group were
in the town.
</P>
<P>
The group is an offshoot of the militant Gama'a al-Islamiya
which has been fighting to establish strict Islamic rule, and was
suspected of involving in attacks on churches in recent months.
</P>
<P>
After the clash, the army surrounded the town and stormed the
group's radio broadcast station. Many militants were arrested, the
statement added. 
</P>
