<HEADLINE> Nagoya Beats Hiroshima to Win Emperor's Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian-born Wagner Lopes and
Yugoslavian international Dragan Stojkovic each scored a goal to
help Nagoya Grampus Eight beat Sanfrecce Hiroshima 2-0 to win the
Emperor's Cup on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Both teams failed to score in the first half.
</P>
<P>
It was Nagoya's second victory in its two appearance in the
final of the Cup, an annual five-week contest among Japan's 80 top
soccer teams. Nagoya's previous win can in 1996, also after
defeating Hiroshima.
</P>
<P>
Stojkovic sent a low cross to Lopes in the 56th minute, before
it was headed home past goalie Takashi Shimoda.
</P>
<P>
Hiroshima launched fierce counter-attacks but, failing to
penetrate Nagoya's defense, could shoot just once after the
interval, against Nagoya's six.
</P>
<P>
Nagoya scored again in a goalmouth melee in the 82nd minute
when Torres passed the ball to Stojkovic, who dribbled past
advancing goalie Shimoda and two defenders before slamming it into
the net.
</P>
<P>
Stojkovic was named the most valuable player of the game.
</P>
<P>
Under team manager Joao Carlos de Silva, Nagoya has won 15
games against one defeat while it was Hiroshima's third loss in
three Emperor's Cup finals following its 3-0 defeats in 1996 and
in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
