<HEADLINE> Macao Newspapers Hail Arrival of Year 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 1 (Xinhua) -- All the major Chinese newspapers
in Macao carried commentaries on Saturday hailing the arrival of
the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Daily News said in an editorial that for the Macao
residents, the past year was one full of expectation and happiness,
as the motherland celebrated the 50th anniversary of her founding,
and Macao returned to the embrace of the motherland at the end of
the year.
</P>
<P>
The 20th century has seen China grow from being weak to strong
and seen China step out of a semi-feudal and semi-colonial society
into an independent country, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Guided by the "one country, two systems" principle initiated by
Deng Xiaoping, China has successfully resolved the Hong Kong
question and Macao question. Taiwan's peaceful reunification with
the motherland will add more glory to the Chinese nation, the
editorial said.
</P>
<P>
The Jornal Va Kio said that the first day of 2000 has brought
about more promises to mankind. Like people around the world, the
Macao residents had flocked to public areas on the eve of the new
year for celebrations to wish for social well-being and economic
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The Dai Chung Pou also noted in a commentary that the grand
celebrations around the world demonstrate that people of all
countries long for peace, stability and prosperity in the new
millennium. People are full of expectations for the future.
</P>
<P>
The Correio Sino-Macaense said in a bylined article that the
year of 1999 not only symbolizes the end of foreign rule in Macao,
but also offers new opportunity. Macao residents should, in the
beginning of a new era, accept challenges and play a more
significant role. 
</P>
</TEXT>
