<HEADLINE> 13 Killed, Hundreds Injured in Festivity Incidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- At least 13 people were killed
and hundreds of others injured in various incidents that marred
Friday night's festivities marking the closing of the 20th Century
in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
According to the Philippine News Agency, five fires hit Metro
Manila, killing nine people. One fire, which claimed the lives of
seven persons, occurred in Caloocan City early Saturday, and the
other, which killed two, occurred in China Town, Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
The agency said a 12-year-old boy was hit by stray bullet and
was taken to the Metropolitan Hospital in Manila where he was
declared dead.
</P>
<P>
One person was killed and two others were wounded in Quezon
City while two were killed in shooting incidents in Marikina City,
it said.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that at least 73 people suffered firecracker
injuries and one was hit by stray bullet and treated in different
hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Department of Health reported that for the period
between December 21 and December 29, three persons had already
been listed as victims of stray bullets while 218 persons were
injured by firecrackers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
