<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Party Leaders Urged to Cherish National Interests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi President Shahabuddin
Ahmed on Saturday morning called upon political leaders and people
from all walks of life to forget individual and party interests
for the sake of greater national interests.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Jatiya Sangsad (parliament) on the inaugural day
session of the new year, the president said: "We must commit
ourselves wholeheartedly to ensure a prosperous and peaceful
Bangladesh for our future generations to realize the dream of '
Sonar Bangla' (Golden Bangladesh) of the father of the nation."
</P>
<P>
"We have created a unique history as a sacrificing nation for
the establishment and preservation of democracy. We must put our
national interest above all other interests to consolidate the
foundation of democracy to bring about economic well-being of the
nation," he said.
</P>
<P>
The presidential address at the start of the first session of
the parliament each year is a constitutional arrangement in the
South Asian nation.
</P>
<P>
The session was then adjourned after the presidential address
to resume on January 12 to continue for the rest of the month.
</P>
<P>
Members of parliament from the opposition parties were absent
from the session.
</P>
<P>
Speaker Humayun Rasheed Chowdhury earlier planned to make the
inaugural session a "millennium session" to welcome the new
millennium, but had to abandon the idea as the opposition, which
had been carrying out a campaign to oust the government, said they
would not join parliament sessions until their demands such as the
implementation of a previous agreement with the ruling party were
met. 
</P>
</TEXT>
