<HEADLINE> Kenyan Police Vows to Protect All </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan police has vowed to
guarantee security of all citizens of the country in the new year
in spirit of police motto "Service to All".
</P>
<P>
Addressing senior officers on Friday, Philemon Abong'o,
Commissioner of Police, announced that his force will intensify
community policing across the country, the state-run Kenya Times
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The measures include the posting of police officers to monitor
security in a given area with strict supervision from their
seniors to contain the crime rate, and embarking on a major public
education to enlighten the public on their rights and how to avoid
criminal activities.
</P>
<P>
"Police officer are to employ more advanced crime prevention
strategies."
</P>
<P>
Abong'o added.
</P>
<P>
He also said that a committee of senior staff will soon be
established to assess the performance of junior officers with a
view to identifying their hidden talents and improving their
service delivery.  
</P>
