<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People Embrace New Year in Different Ways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- People of the Chinese mainland
greeted the new year and bade farewell to the past millennium in
their own ways.
</P>
<P>
Residents and tourists in Harbin, capital of northeast's
Heilongjiang Province, at midnight jammed into a newly-built ice-
and-snow park to hear ringing of a bell specially placed atop a 33-
meter-high ice tower greeting the arrival of the new year, and to
watch the play of fireworks.
</P>
<P>
The park covers an area of 200,000 sq m and costs more than 30
million yuan, said local sources.
</P>
<P>
Residents of Tianjin on the rim of Bohai Gulf held gatherings,
rang a huge bell with a weight of 1.06 tons, or blew sirens to
hail the footsteps of the new year.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Li Shenglin lighted a major torch for a long-distance
torch race at the Tianjin Gymnasium at midnight and Party
Secretary Zhang Lichang offered local residents a new year message.
</P>
<P>
Fifty Chinese and Japanese students greeted the new year in
this Chinese capital of Beijing by successfully pushing over all 2.
5 million Domino pieces six minutes before the midnight,
refreshing the previous record of 2.47 million pieces mentioned
in the Guinness Book of Records.
</P>
<P>
Down south, more than 1,200 tourists coming from Japan, Italy,
Spain and Austria joined a crowd of 30,000 people at 1,400 year-
old Hanshan Temple in Suzhou City, Jiangsu Province to hear bells
ringing at the midnight, warmly embracing the new year and praying
for world peace and good luck.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan on the middle reaches of the mighty Yangtze River ushered
into this new year by ringing a bell placed at the 1,700-year-old
Yellow Crane Tower and the 2,400 year-old chime bells of the Chu
Kingdom from the Spring and Autumn Warring Kingdoms period, as
well as sounding of a big clock placed atop Wuhan Customs Building.
</P>
<P>
On the last day of 1999, Urumqi, capital of northwest China's
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, was a world of snow, and 40
couples in the city chose a mass wedding ceremony to tie knots,
wishing for a good marriage and good luck in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Amid the footsteps of the new year, four babies, all male, came
to the world as the first this year, respectively, in Lhasa on the
roof of the world, Lanzhou of northwest China's Gansu Province,
Nanjing of Jiangsu and Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
