<HEADLINE> Adventurer Cross China's Lowest Point </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, WESTERN CHINA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese
adventurer has successfully completed human being's first solo
motorcycle crossing of the dried bed of the Aiding Lake, which is
China's lowest point.
</P>
<P>
Located at the base of the Tulufan Basin of the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region, the Aiding Lake, which means "Moonlight Lake"
in Uygurian, is seated 154 meters below sea level. The lake has
an area of 22 square kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Starting from the northern bank at 16:40 hour PM Friday on a
motorcycle, Cui Di crossed the lake's dried-up bed to the southern
bank and rode back along the same nine-kilometer route to the
starting point after one hour 46 minutes. The solo crossing
coincided with the last sunset of the 20th century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
