<HEADLINE> Heavy Snowfall Causes Trouble to Traffic in Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- A heavy snowfall across Bulgaria
since Friday has made traffic difficult, the government said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
However the overall situation around the country is normal for
winter, said the Standing Governmental Commission for the
Management of Natural Disasters and Industrial Accidents.
</P>
<P>
Several flights of the Balkan Airlines have been canceled due
to snowfall, a spokesman of the airlines said.
</P>
<P>
Traffic was blocked for hours Friday along the E 79
international road exit from Sofia to Southwestern Bulgaria and
the roads and passes in Zlatitsa, Tvurditsa, Dyulin, Troyan-
Kurnare and Shipkovo-Ribaritsa were closed.
</P>
<P>
The roads in low-lying parts of the Smolyan, Ivailovgrad and
Svilengrad regions have been flooded. In many places visibility
was reduced to 100 meters due to snow and fog.
</P>
<P>
Power outages were reported in 105 population centers and
several population centers were also without water and electricity
supply.
</P>
<P>
The snowcover was reported at between 15 and 70 centimeters,
the thickest being in southwestern and southeastern Bulgaria.
</P>
