<HEADLINE> Indonesia Peacefully Welcomes New Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Abdurrahman Wahid witnessed the first sun rise in the
easternmost province of Irian Jaya Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In his address welcoming the year 2000, Wahid called on the
nation to enter the new millennium with a resolve to utilize
technology for the benefit of man.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian nation must be able to enter the year 2000 with
a determination to develop technology, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The celebration of the New Year in Jayapura, capital of Irian
Jaya,ran smoothly with sounds of fireworks and trumpets heard
across the city.
</P>
<P>
In Jakarta, at least a million people took to the streets and
their thousands of vehicles clogged the downtown, causing the
traffic to come to a standstill a few hours before midnight.
</P>
<P>
As the clock turned to 00:00 hours, January 1, 2000 and the
bright lights were still on, marking that the electrical grid was
functioning normally and free from the attack of the millennium
bug, the sounds of plastic trumpets and firecrackers filled the
air.
</P>
<P>
Apart from minor injuries sustained by some people from light
traffic accidents or firecrackers, there were no serious accidents
or civil disobedience recorded by the Jakarta Police Headquarters
until Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
In Mataram, capital of West Nusa Tenggara, thousands of Muslims
performed mass prayers in a number of mosques to welcome the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
As the New Year 2000 coincided with the fasting month of
Ramadan,the local authorities did not hold any activity to
celebrate the New Year's eve.
</P>
<P>
In riot-torn Ambon, capital of Maluku province, the new
millennium celebration was colored by tension and a barrage of
attacks on a number of residences in the city.
</P>
<P>
Tension was reported to have spread to a number of places in
the center of the city where masses began to be seen to carry self-
made bombs and weapons. Strong explosion of self-made bombs was
frequently heard on some locations.
</P>
<P>
Security personnel deployed to some conflict-stricken locations
and demarcation zones of conflicting groups have taken severe
measures by releasing warning shots with an aim to disperse the
masses, thus avoid possible physical contact. 
</P>
</TEXT>
