<HEADLINE> Kenya Takes Measures to Revive Economy in New Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Kenya is taking new measures to
reverse the downturn of the country's economy in the new year,
Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi said in his new millennium
speech.
</P>
<P>
"We have gone through lean times economically, but I'm
confident that with the measures taken by the government, Kenya's
economy will soon recover," Moi said in his 20-minute new year
message broadcast on television at midnight Friday.
</P>
