<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's inflation rate in
1999 averaged 2.01 percent or way below the previous year's figure
of 77.63 percent, according to the Antara News Agency Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Improvements in the economic and political situations this
year influenced the inflation rate in a favorable way so that it
dropped to far below the previous year's figure," chief of the
Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) Sugito Suwito said.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate stood at 1.73 in December 1999, while it was
0.25 in November.
</P>
<P>
