<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, January 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The two leaders spoke for about 20 minutes. Clinton saluted
Russia's movement to democracy under Yeltsin and pledged to work
with the Russian people, Acting President Vladimir Putin, the
winner of next year's presidential election, Lockhart said.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The first plane load of
passengers released from the hijacked Indian Airlines plane landed
in Delhi at 8:42 p.m. local time Friday.
</P>
<P>
Heavy security arrangements were made in and around the airport
to ward off any trouble.
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- Panama recovered Friday at midday the
sovereignty over the interoceanic waterway, after 85 years of U.S.
military occupation.
</P>
<P>
Panama recovered full sovereignty over the Canal Zone in
compliance with the Torrijos-Carter Treaties signed in 1977 by the
Panama and United States governments.
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on Friday
wrote a letter to Boris Yeltsin after he announced stepping down
as president of the Russian Federation.
</P>
<P>
In the letter, Annan pledged to work closely with Acting
President Vladimir Putin.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's resignation after eight years and a half as
president was seen widely by political analysts as a boost to
Putin's chances of winning the presidency in an early elections
due on March 26, 2000.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Acting President Vladimir Putin on Friday
signed a decree providing security guarantees for Boris Yeltsin,
who stepped down earlier in the day as the Russian head of state.
</P>
<P>
The decree makes immediate provisions for "legal, social
security and other guarantees" for one who has left office as
president "due to the expiry of his term... or who has resigned
before such a date or who has displayed a steady inability for
health reasons to exercise his powers" and for "members of his
family."
</P>
<P>
It is reported that one of the key conditions for Yeltsin's
early resignation is the provision of security guarantees for
himself and his family after he leaves the Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan was greatly
relieved that the hijacking of an Indian plane ended peacefully
without further loss of life, U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard said on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 154 passengers and crew were freed at Kandahar airport, in
Afghanistan, after a week-long ordeal. They were released after
India freed three jailed kashmiri militants.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- There will be no "vacuum of power" in Russia "for a
minute or even a second" after ex-president Boris Yeltsin's
resignation, said Russian Acting President Vladimir Putin in his
New Year address to the nation on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"Any attempt to overstep the federal Constitution will be cut
short resolutely" and the Russians will be able to exercise all
their rights, Putin said in the televised address. 
</P>
