<HEADLINE> Cambodians Stride Into New Millennium With Boundless Joy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SIEM REAP, Cambodia January 1 (Xinhua) -- Like the people
throughout the world, Cambodians strode into the new millennium
with full of new hope.
</P>
<P>
When Prince Norodom Ranariddh, president of the National
Assembly, announced the passing of the old millennium and the
arrival of the third millennium, the whole Angkor Wat was seething
with excitement.
</P>
<P>
At this time of rejoicing, 2,000 Buddhist monks began to offer
their blessing to greet the new year, new millennium. People were
enjoying a colorful fireworks display and the sound of drums. Some
200 traditional flying lanterns were launched into the sky.
</P>
<P>
The prince called on the whole country to work together to
maintain the peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
"We will also work together with those peace-loving countries
and the United Nations as well as international organizations to
develop the culture of peace," Ranariddh said.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia held a three-day grand celebration from Thursday in
front of Angkor Wat to greet the new year, new century and the new
millennium.
</P>
<P>
King Norodom Sihanouk and Queen Monineath Sihanouk, greeting
the new millennium at the Royal Palace in the capital Phnom Penh,
also sent their blessing to the countrymen and their good wishes
for a successful, safe and joyful Angkor-2000 Festival.
</P>
<P>
All senior government officials were at present, including
Senate President Chea Sim and Prime Minister Hun Sen.
</P>
