<BODY>
<HEADLINE> N.Z. Opens Up Worldwide Millennium Celebrations(3)  By Zhou Cipu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the moment when the globe began entering the new millennium,
a stunning fireworks display set the Auckland skyline afire at
midnight. Shot from inner-city high-rise buildings including the
Sky Tower, the multicolorful fireworks display ran for 12 minutes.
</P>
<P>
A large-scale concert was staged at Auckland's Okahu Domain.
People at the Okahu Domain adopted a unique form to bid farewell
to the old millennium by standing in silence during last moments
of darkness. A few minutes later, a giant flotilla of more than 2,
000 craft including Maori canoes, dragon boats, naval ships and
Pacific Island outriggers sailed by. A royal New Zealand Air Force
fly-by extended the spectacle to the air.
</P>
<P>
At 6:06 am, the millennium flotilla arrived at the shores of
Okahu Bay as the first rays of sunlight stroke the water. Conches
call from the shore as a formal Maori welcome was sung across the
bay and a 2,000-strong welcome party performed the biggest ever
haka (a traditional Maori dance).
</P>
<P>
New Zealand Governor-General Sir Michael Hardie Boys attended
Wellington celebrations to welcome in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
In order to add more international significance to its
celebrations, the capital of New Zealand invited more than 150
teenagers from 80 countries and regions to take part in its
celebrations. They gathered with nearly 2,000 local children in a
pre-dawn ceremony of music and dance on the top of Mt Victoria,
the highest point of the city. Seeing the dawn coming, the happy
children broke into deafening cheers. A dozen of teenagers in
Japanese kimonos jubilantly beat taiko drums to greet the arrival
of new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Wellington is also a coastal city. A water-front carnival went
from the new year's eve through to the dawn. A great number of
Wellingtoners, braving the rain and bringing along the old and the
young, attended the exciting event. On the seaside, which was
decorated with tens of thousands of colorful lights, they enjoyed
performances by local artists, fireworks displays and a dance
party. The celebrations in Wellington left people with an
unforgetable impression.
</P>
<P>
On the new year's eve and dawn, the whole of New Zealand was
permeated with a festive atmosphere. Various forms of activities
were organized to bid farewell to the outgoing millennium and
welcome in the incoming one, including mountain-climbing to greet
the dawn, bay-crossing swimming, food stalls, lantern parades,
collective wedding ceremonies, and sports games.
</P>
<P>
During the occasion, a song, composed especially for the
millennium celebrations in New Zealand was sung. The song entitled
"I'll Meet You There" urged people to be optimistic about the
future and greet the new millennium in high spirit. It told the
people that their dreams could be realized as long as they never
thought of "turning back."
</P>
<P>
An official of the New Zealand Millennium Office told Xinhua
that the four millennium Touchstones had travelled the whole
country to listen to people's wishes and dreams. Although each had
his or her own wishes and dreams, a common wish was shared. They
all wished the new millennium would bring peace, harmony,
prosperity and happiness to the troubled world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
