<HEADLINE> Macao People Greet New Millennium with Great  Expectations  By Zhang Yongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Like people around the world,
throngs of residents in Macao began flocking to public areas on
the eve of the new millennium, and celebrations heated up to high
tides toward midnight.
</P>
<P>
During the last several hours of 1999, Macao was illuminated
and lively songs and cheers could be heard all around the region
which had been reunited with the motherland just a dozen days ago.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR)
government and social bodies, countdown soirees were held at
several public places.
</P>
<P>
A torch was lit up in front of the famous Ruins of St. Paul
Church. Holding candles, hundreds of local middle-school students
were arrayed on the steps, singing for the upcoming new year. The
lights of the torch and candles blended with the colorfully
decorated lights nearby.
</P>
<P>
In the form of a zigzagging human chain, residents passed on
water, fire, soil and air -- which are regarded as four
fundamental elements to nurture life -- to a downtown square
several hundred meters away.
</P>
<P>
The square was overcrowded. Art performances brought people
nearer and nearer to the exhilarating moment. The performances
started from about half past nine on the eve of the new year.
</P>
<P>
The midnight was coming and people counted down loudly, "ten,
nine, eight,...... two, one!" Thunderous cheering erupted from the
square while thousands of balloons which bore people's written
best wishes were released into the air.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, celebrating soirees were in full swing in
many places.
</P>
<P>
In front of the Macao Jockey Club, singers from China's
Guangdong Province, Hong Kong as well as Macao sang for the new
year. Crowds of people were also fascinated by passionate dancing
and conjuring. Children were wild with joy holding the new year
gifts they had received from game stands.
</P>
<P>
Inside the Macao Forum, which had accommodated a grand party on
December 20 to mark the founding of the Macao SAR, about 5,000
people watched performances and waited for the coming of the new
year.
</P>
<P>
Along the southern coastal area of Macao, hundreds of
bicyclists from around the world held a competition around
midnight. It was part of a series of bicycling contests
surrounding the South China Sea.
</P>
<P>
Macao people have marched into a new year, a new era indeed,
just as Chinese President Jiang Zemin pointed out at Macao's
handover ceremony right after China's national flag was raised in
the territory which had long been ruled by the Portuguese. 
</P>
</TEXT>
