<HEADLINE> People Across China Greet New Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China celebrated the new
millennium with colorful festivities throughout the land.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, the largest industrial center of China, greeted the
new millennium with a colorful fireworks display, lively lion
dancing and grand gala along the Huangpu River.
</P>
<P>
Local residents counted down the last ten seconds of the
millennium in unison. When the clock clicked to the zero hour,
people in the crowd hugged and cheered wildly.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing, the youngest municipality in southwest China,
welcomed the arrival of the year 2000 with a motorcycle rally at
dawn today.
</P>
<P>
People holding torches bearing the numbers "1999" ran in front
of the procession, followed by 2,000 motorcycles and 2,000 long
distance runners.
</P>
<P>
The procession passed through a 1,000-meter tunnel decorated
with 1,362 lights and a board brightly lit with the number 2000,
symbolizing the Chinese people's march from one millennium to
another.
</P>
<P>
High school student Cao Junjie said, "I am proud to be a
representative of 1.2 million students in our city of Chongqing to
greet the new millennium."
</P>
<P>
Nankai University in north China port city of Tianjin hosted a
grand evening party tonight. Thousands of students performed
dances with red silk banners in their hands before large-screen
TVs or the countdown clock.
</P>
<P>
A 115-year-old woman in a village on Tianjin's western
outskirts observed the festive night at her own home with five
generations of her family, more than 60 people in total. The city
boasts 92 centenarians who have entered the new century.
</P>
<P>
In northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region,
approximately 60 people from the United States, Hong Kong, Beijing
and Shanghai gathered at the Taklimakan Desert, the largest desert
of its kind in China, to see the first sunrise of this century.
They cheered, rang bells and released pigeons and balloons.
</P>
<P>
Among them were 10 newly-recovered patients who are all around
age 60 and eight couples who will hold their wedding ceremony on
the desert when the first rays of sunlight appear.
</P>
<P>
In freezing Harbin, capital of China's northernmost
Heilongjiang Province, 34 couples from the U.S., Turkey and China
held their wedding ceremony in a lavish artistic project named the
"Great World of Ice and Snow."
</P>
<P>
However, many residents in south China's Guangzhou city who
usually travel during holidays chose to stay at home on the first
day of 2000 for fear of possible Y2K problems with airlines. Some
said they will visit nearby scenic spots by bus instead of flying.
</P>
<P>
A luxury pleasure cruiser named the "Millennium Boat" carried
people from all social strata down the Beijing-Hangzhou Great
Canal, which winds through four provinces and two major cities
with a total length of 1,789 meters. Passengers sang and danced
joyously to celebrate the arrival of the year 2000. They are
scheduled to see the first ray of the new millennium on Guangji
Bridge.  
</P>
</TEXT>
