<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Airports Hits Annual Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai airports Friday
reported a record high annual flight, passenger and cargo total.
</P>
<P>
Till the last day of 1999, the number of flights stood at 139,
000, passengers, 14.74 million, and freight, 769,000 tons, a rise
of 8.57, 7.46 and 34.39 percent respectively over 1998.
</P>
<P>
For the past year, Shanghai airports have taken steps to
improve management and service. Hongqiao Airport changed the old
flight arrival/departure screen with one that displays flight
information more clearly. Three hundred new-style luggage carts
are available free of charge. A customer satisfaction system has
been put in place to ensure every passenger is taken care of.
</P>
<P>
Hongqiao Airport, together with the newly-built Pudong Airport,
received certificates of honor from the Municipal Government for
their excellent performance.
</P>
<P>
All sections of the airports have been working to eliminate
fire hazards. Both airports have passed safety appraisal by China'
s General Administration of Civil Aviation (CAAC) and gained
approval from American Federal Aviation Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Till now, Hongqiao Airport has flights to 97 world cities, and
42 aviation companies from home and overseas have opened routes to
Hongqiao Airport.  
</P>
</TEXT>
