<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Greets New Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina on Friday greeted the nation and people all over the
world on the even of the new year, new century and third
millennium wishing victory of humanity and peace across the globe
in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
"I convey my hearty congratulations to all members of human
race as well as the countrymen on the eve of the new year, 21st
century and the third millennium beginning with endless
possibilities of development, progress and solidarity," she said
in a message.
</P>
<P>
"We are excited to welcome the New World of the new millennium .
.. We are expressing our firm determination to stand before the
world with dignity in the new millennium," she said.
</P>
<P>
Hasina termed as a historic event the recognition of February
21 (by UNESCO in November 1999) as the International Mother
Language Day in the recognition of the Bengali nation's sacrifice
for the mother tongue.
</P>
<P>
"Our success in restoring peace in the Chittagong Hill Tracts,
the signing of the Ganges water sharing treaty and its
implementation and our policy of economic diplomacy and endeavor
for world peace have been praised across the globe," she said.
</P>
<P>
In the new millennium, she said, Bangladesh wants to work hand
in hand with other countries to build a world free from poverty,
hunger and pollution joining the common struggle for ensuring
education, health, accommodation for all.
</P>
<P>
"In the mew millennium, I wish the world be habitable for all
children and the deprived women come to the limelight. Let all the
unemployed join the stream of production and prosperity." she said.
</P>
