<HEADLINE> Urgent: No Y2K Problems Found Yet in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China entered the new millennium
apparently free from the bite of Y2K problems in major sectors,
according to an official of the China Y2K Problem Contingency
Office.
</P>
<P>
There have been no reports of any computer bug problems from
the majority of the country's 20 major fields, including civil
aviation, power grid, maritime transportation, banking and
securities services, as well as public security and state security
departments, the official said, adding that his office still
collects data from across the country.  
