<HEADLINE> Beijing Concert to Greet 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The curtain rose on a New Year
's concert tonight at the Great Hall of the People, a highlight of
the new millennium celebrations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing, together with people from all
walks of life in the capital, attended the concert to greet the
upcoming new century.
</P>
<P>
Two major Chinese choral ensembles, two prestigious symphony
orchestras, and dozens of domestic artists and overseas Chinese
musicians staged a program themed on welcoming the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Many famous Western musical numbers and opera pieces were also
played, as well as modern Chinese compositions focusing on the
country's opening and reform and the people's confidence in a
bright 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The concert was jointly sponsored by the Beijing municipal
government, the Ministry of Culture, and the State Administration
of Radio, Film and Television.
</P>
<P>
This annual event, given prior to the Chinese Lunar New Year or
Spring Festival, has been held since 1996.  
