<HEADLINE> Macao to Issue New Postal Product on 1st Day of 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The Postal and Telecommunication
Services (PTS) of the Macao Special Administrative Region SAR)
government will begin the issuance of a new set of postal product
entitled "Macao, a New Era".
</P>
<P>
The set includes a souvenir sheet with one stamp worth eight
patacas (one U.S. dollar), a first-day envelop worth four patacas
and a piece of introduction sheet worth 4.5 patacas, PTS Director
Carlos Alberto Roldao Lopes said at a press conference on Friday.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first of 12 sets of postal products which the
PTS plans to issue in the new year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a notice announced by the PTS says that all
previous stamps issued by the Portuguese government, except the
transitional set entitled "modern architecture", have ceased to
be valid in circulation beginning from December 20, when the
Chinese government resumed the exercise of sovereignty over Macao.
</P>
<P>
However, holders of the old stamps can barter for new stamps
having the same face value from January 2 to 31 of 2000, the
notice says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
