<HEADLINE> Chronology of Hijacking of Indian Plane (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
...negotiations with the hijackers
</P>
<P>
December 27:
</P>
<P>
- Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee holds meeting with the
opposition leaders
</P>
<P>
- External Affairs Minister Jaswant Singh announces that an
Indian delegation will hold talks with the hijackers
</P>
<P>
- A special plane carrying negotiators, doctors and engineers
leaves the military airport in Dubai at 15:40 hours for Kandahar
</P>
<P>
- The special plane returns after being air-borne for eight
minutes following a technical snag
</P>
<P>
- The special plane leaves again at 16:39 hours for Kandahar,
arrives at 18:20 hours at the southern Afghan city airport
</P>
<P>
- Hold talks with the Taliban authorities
</P>
<P>
December 28:
</P>
<P>
- Engineers and technicians of Indian delegation are allowed
to rectify snag in the fuselage of the seized aircraft
</P>
<P>
- One of the hijackers steps out of IC-814 for the first time
to hold direct talks with the negotiators
</P>
<P>
- Indian engineer allowed to rectify the snags in the hijacked
plane
</P>
<P>
- Hijackers release a list of demands besides 200 million U.S.
dollars
</P>
<P>
- Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee holds meeting with three
service chiefs
</P>
<P>
- Several countries including the United States condemn
hijacking of the plane
</P>
<P>
- Some passengers of the ill-fated plane take a stroll for the
first time since hijacking on December 24
</P>
</TEXT>
