<HEADLINE> Celebration Greeting New Millennium Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua)-- The grand celebration to greet
the new millennium came to an end early this morning amid a joyful
and ardent atmosphere in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The celebration, which was jointly organized by the Communist
Party of China Committee of Beijing, the Beijing municipal
government, and the National Tourism Administration at the China
Centenary Altar in western Beijing lasted for 48 minutes.
</P>
<P>
A total of 25,000 people took part in the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Actors and actresses from mainland China, the Hong Kong and
Macao special administrative regions, and Taiwan, performed a
Millennium Pageant, a spectacular singing and dancing program
expressing the joy of the Chinese people in welcoming the new
century and their earnest expectations for greater progress in the
years ahead.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
