<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Lights Sacred Flame </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
lighted a sacred flame here tonight on the occasion of Beijing's
celebrations greeting the new century and millennium.
</P>
<P>
At 23:59, President Jiang pressed a button lighting the "sacred
flame of China" made from kindling collected from the Zhoukoudian,
the site of "Peking Man," in southwest Beijing. The flame is
intended to burn forever symbolizing the continuous civilization
of the Chinese nation throughout the generations.
</P>
<P>
The Zhoukoudian Pithecanthropus Site was discovered in 1927.
Archeologists say mankind who three million years ago lived in the
region that now is China discovered fire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
