<DOCNO> XIE20000101.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Praises Yeltsin's Efforts to Promote Bilateral Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- China highly appreciates Boris
Yeltsin's ceaseless efforts to promote Sino-Russian relations
during his tenure as Russian president, Foreign Ministry spokesman
Zhu Bangzao said here tonight.
</P>
<P>
When commenting on Yeltsin's resignation earlier today, Zhu
said China believes that President Yeltsin's resignation is an
internal affair of Russia.
</P>
<P>
Zhu added that as a friendly neighbor of Russia, "We sincerely
hope that Russia will maintain stability and development."
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that during Yeltsin's tenure as Russian president, he
made unremitting efforts to establish and promote Sino-Russian
strategic and cooperative partnership, laying a good foundation
for the further growth of bilateral relations in the years ahead.
</P>
<P>
"China highly appreciates this," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that through joint efforts, Sino-Russian relations
will achieve even greater success in the new century," Zhu said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
